<TITLE> Marina Mahathir in Dhaka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 11 (bdnews24.com)  Marina Mahathir, a human-rights activist and daughter of Malaysia's former prime minister Mahathir Mohammad, arrived in Dhaka Sunday midnight on a six-day visit. "Marina arrived in Dhaka at 12.10am by a Malaysia Airlines aircraft," Daily Amader Shomoy editor Nayeemul Islam Khan told bdnews24.com by telephone. Khan and officials from the Malaysian High Commission received her at Zia International Airport. Marina is scheduled to take part in a seminar on media and gender equity and visit some health, education and microcredit projects run by Grameen Bank and BRAC. She is set to meet foreign adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury Monday afternoon and with president Iajuddin Ahmed and chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed later. Bangladesh Centre for Development, Journalism and Communication (BCDJC) in a press statement on Saturday said Marina was coming to Dhaka at its invitation to give a talk on media and gender equity. She would also join some programmes on business coalition on HIV/AIDS programme of the UNAID and Asian University of Women (AUW), Chittagong. Marina is a popular columnist of Malaysian English daily The Star. As a member of the National Women's Advisory Council, she advices the Malaysian government on women affairs. She is also involved with service-oriented organisations like AIDS Foundation, Women's Aid Organisation and Sisters in Islam. Marina's 3R, a programme on women health, career, information and technology, aired on Malaysian Television has earned national and international awards since 2000. She is one of the most influential bloggers of Malaysia. bdne
